# Design System: The Initiated

**Project ID:** the-initiated
**Platform:** Android (Jetpack Compose) + Web (React/Tailwind)

## 1. Visual Theme & Atmosphere

Dark, bold, and editorial — athletic energy channeled through premium design. Card-heavy layouts with striking imagery, gold accent moments, and confident typography. The aesthetic sits between a sports magazine and a luxury brand lookbook. Deep navy backgrounds create depth while gold highlights draw the eye to key actions. Despite the boldness, readability is never sacrificed — generous line height and careful contrast ratios keep content scannable.

## 2. Color Palette & Roles

### Dark Mode (Primary)
- **Initiated Gold** (#C9A84C) — primary actions, CTAs, highlights, badges, brand accent
- **On Gold Dark** (#1A1A2E) — text and icons on gold surfaces
- **Deep Navy** (#1B2A4A) — primary surface, card backgrounds, main canvas
- **Darker Navy** (#111B30) — page backgrounds, deepest layer
- **Soft White** (#F1F5F9) — primary text, headings
- **Muted Silver** (#94A3B8) — secondary text, metadata, timestamps
- **Navy Border** (#2D3F5E) — subtle dividers, card borders
- **White Surface** (#FFFFFF) — rare light accent surfaces, avatar rings
- **Alert Red** (#EF4444) — error states, elimination indicators
- **Success Emerald** (#10B981) — success states, advancement indicators
- **Info Blue** (#3B82F6) — informational callouts, links

### Light Mode (Secondary)
- **Initiated Gold** (#C9A84C) — primary accent (consistent with dark mode)
- **On Gold Dark** (#1A1A2E) — text on gold surfaces
- **Light Surface** (#F8FAFC) — page backgrounds
- **White** (#FFFFFF) — card backgrounds
- **Near Black** (#0F172A) — primary text
- **Slate** (#64748B) — secondary text
- **Light Border** (#E2E8F0) — dividers, separators

## 3. Typography Rules

- **Display Font:** Bebas Neue — used exclusively for hero headlines, athlete names, event titles. All uppercase. Never for body text.
- **Body Font:** Inter — all body text, labels, buttons, navigation, metadata
- **Fallback:** system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif
- **Display Large:** Bebas Neue, 48px / Regular (400) — hero headlines, event names
- **Display Medium:** Bebas Neue, 36px / Regular (400) — section titles, athlete spotlights
- **Headline Large:** Inter, 28px / Bold (700) — screen titles, card headings
- **Headline Medium:** Inter, 22px / SemiBold (600) — section headers
- **Body Large:** Inter, 16px / Regular (400) — primary content, descriptions
- **Body Medium:** Inter, 14px / Regular (400) — secondary content, card descriptions
- **Label Large:** Inter, 14px / SemiBold (600) — button text, tab labels
- **Label Medium:** Inter, 12px / Medium (500) — metadata, captions, stat labels
- **Letter Spacing:** Bebas Neue: 0.05em (wide tracking for display). Inter: normal for body, -0.01em for headlines.
- **Line Height:** 1.6 for body (generous for readability on dark backgrounds), 1.1 for Bebas Neue display.

## 4. Spacing Scale

- **Base unit:** 4px grid
- **xs:** 4px — tight gaps between inline elements, stat label spacing
- **sm:** 8px — compact card internal padding, badge spacing
- **md:** 16px — standard card padding, content margins
- **lg:** 24px — section gaps, card-to-card spacing
- **xl:** 32px — major section separators, screen-level padding
- **2xl:** 48px — hero section vertical padding, page margins

## 5. Elevation & Depth

- **Level 0:** Flat — flush with surface (inline content, list items)
- **Level 1:** Subtle glow — `0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.3)` (cards on dark background)
- **Level 2:** Soft depth — `0 4px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.4)` (featured cards, popovers)
- **Level 3:** Pronounced — `0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.5)` (modals, overlays)
- **Level 4:** Dramatic — `0 12px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.6)` (full-screen takeovers)
- **Level 5:** Deep — `0 20px 48px rgba(0,0,0,0.7)` (hero image overlays)

Strategy: Shadows are bolder on dark backgrounds to maintain visual separation. Use darker rgba values than typical light-mode systems.

## 6. Component Defaults

- **Buttons:** Medium rounding (8px), 48px height. Primary uses gold background with dark text. Secondary uses outlined with gold border on navy. Ghost buttons for tertiary actions.
- **Cards:** Editorial layout — 12px rounding, navy background, full-bleed images with gradient overlays. Cards are the primary content vessel. Standard card: image top (60% height), content bottom (40%).
- **Athlete Cards:** Special variant — large hero image with gradient overlay, Bebas Neue name overlay, stat chips at bottom.
- **Inputs:** 48px height, 8px radius, navy-dark background (#111B30), 1px navy-border, gold focus ring. Placeholder text in muted silver.
- **Navigation:** Bottom tab bar (mobile), side nav (web). Active state: gold icon + label. Inactive: muted silver.
- **Chips/Badges:** Pill-shaped (full radius), 28px height. Gold background for active/featured, navy-border for inactive.
- **Icon Size:** 24px standard, 20px inline, 32px navigation.
- **Touch Targets:** 48x48dp minimum.

## 7. Motion & Animation

- **Fast:** 150ms — button feedback, chip toggles, icon transitions
- **Medium:** 300ms — card reveals, tab transitions, content fades
- **Slow:** 500ms — hero image transitions, page-level animations, spotlight reveals
- **Easing Standard:** cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)
- **Easing Decelerate:** cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1) — content entering view
- **Easing Accelerate:** cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1) — content exiting
- **Special:** Card flip animation for athlete reveals (800ms, spring easing)
- **Reduced Motion:** Respect system preference. Replace animations with instant state changes.

## 8. Platform Notes

### Android (Compose)
- MaterialTheme with custom dark ColorScheme
- Bebas Neue loaded via Google Fonts Compose integration
- Bottom navigation with 4 tabs: Home, Discover, Events, Profile
- Swipe gestures on athlete cards (swipe to save/dismiss)

### Web (React/Tailwind)
- Dark mode as default (`class="dark"` on html element)
- Bebas Neue via Google Fonts (`@import`)
- Responsive: mobile-first, breakpoints at 768px and 1024px
- Sidebar navigation on desktop, bottom tabs on mobile viewport

## 9. Locale & Accessibility Notes

- **Primary Locale:** en-US (English)
- **RTL Support:** Not required initially. Flag: false
- **Number Format:** Comma for thousands, period for decimals: `1,500.00`
- **Date Format:** MMM DD, YYYY (e.g., "Mar 19, 2026")
- **Accessibility Level:** WCAG AA minimum
- **Dark Mode Contrast:** Gold (#C9A84C) on navy (#1B2A4A) = 4.8:1 ratio (passes AA for large text). For small text, use Soft White (#F1F5F9) on navy = 11.2:1 ratio.
- **Image Alt Text:** All athlete photos require descriptive alt text including name and action
- **Screen Reader:** Card content must be announced as a single group with title, subtitle, and action
